cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection in images using a deep neural network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architecture and training of the neural network, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multiple feature maps and aspect ratios suggests the use of neural networks with multiple layers and possibly convolutional neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the method on various datasets, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
